children.subject: They're the same thing; CSM Tech is the name of the team, and Tech Mentor is the name of the role.
Two roles in CSM Tech: Tech Chair (team leads) and Tech Mentors
What's the difference between joining CSM Tech and being a Tech Mentor? I'm not too familiar with Django and Typescript, and it says to consider being a tech mentor.

history.content:
Hey everyone, CSM Tech is recruiting again!!!

CSM is one of the largest student-led teaching organizations in the country. As our club grows, our tech infrastructure will need to grow alongside it. CSM Tech is small but growing, and we are looking to expand our team to create a larger impact on the general edtech community at Berkeley. We would love to have you join us!

Tech Mentor is a dedicated role in CSM where the mentor will be working directly with the Tech Chair & current Tech Mentors to fix bugs, maintain Scheduler / CSM’s website, and build out new and cool features to make CSM even better.

Due to CSM’s size, the work you do in CSM Tech will have a large and lasting impact on the Berkeley CS community.

We have established onboarding materials, guides, and senior tech mentors to help you get up to speed with our codebase while learning web dev.

Apply Here! -- Applications are due Friday, November 12th 11:59 pm

You can read more about this role in the Tech Mentor Description doc.
history.subject: APPLY TO CSM TECH !!!!!
